articles.title: Gabon military officers claim to have seized power after election - CNN
articles.description: Military officers on Wednesday declared they were seizing power in Gabon, shortly after President Ali Bongo was deemed the victor of a contested election, extending his family’s half-century rule over the Central African nation.
